  {a:'VST', b:'AI-capex', v:0.4, sg:1, ch:'BEAR-CASE LINK: power-demand thesis is downstream of AI capex; VST sold off in the DeepSeek capex-doubt shock despite no change to current load.', src:'public'},
  {a:'CEG', b:'AI-capex', v:0.4, sg:1, ch:'BEAR-CASE LINK: datacenter-PPA re-rating is contingent on the AI build-out continuing; de-rates if AI capex stalls.', src:'public'},
  {a:'GEV', b:'AI-capex', v:0.35, sg:1, ch:'BEAR-CASE LINK: turbine/grid order-book optimism is tied to sustained AI datacenter spend.', src:'public'},
  {a:'VRT', b:'AI-capex', v:0.45, sg:1, ch:'BEAR-CASE LINK: datacenter thermal/power demand is a direct function of AI capex; falls with the accelerator trade.', src:'public'},
  {a:'SKH', b:'HBM-memory', v:0.95, sg:1, ch:'HBM market-share leader and lead supplier to NVIDIA; the purest HBM-cycle stock (record Q3-24 profit on HBM/AI demand).', src:'public'},
  {a:'MU', b:'HBM-memory', v:0.7, sg:1, ch:'HBM3E ramp is the re-rating driver, but a large commodity DRAM/NAND base ties it to the broader memory cycle, diluting pure-HBM beta.', src:'public'},
  {a:'SMSN', b:'HBM-memory', v:0.55, sg:1, ch:'HBM upside is real but it is the share-loser/laggard in HBM qualification, and a huge diversified franchise (foundry/handset/display) dilutes transmission.', src:'public'},
  {a:'HANMI', b:'HBM-memory', v:0.95, sg:1, ch:'Dominant TC-bonder supplier for HBM stacking; a near-pure HBM-capex equipment proxy — stock is one of the highest-beta HBM plays.', src:'public'},
